@pfeatherstone we have 3 different LR groups for 0) weights 1) batch_norm layers 2) biases.

The weights are trained normally, the batch_norm layers are trained without weight_decay, and the biases are trained without weight decay and also more aggressively at the beginning during the prebias/burnin (biases are more stable to higher LRs than weights).

And yes they all have momentum/nesterov.

@pfeatherstone ah yes you are right, it is almost exactly the same!
https://pytorch.org/docs/stable/optim.html#torch.optim.lr_scheduler.OneCycleLR

Maybe if I have some time I can integrate the onecycle scheduler in place of the current system...
